						<div class="vers-content">So they came to Bethsaida. And they brought to him a blind man, whom they entreated him to touch.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers173633" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">23</div>
						<div class="vers-content">He took the blind man by the hand, and led him outside the village; then he spat into his eyes, and laid his hands on him, and asked him if he could see anything?</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers173634" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">24</div>
						<div class="vers-content">He looked up and said, I can see men as if they were trees, but walking.</div>
					</div>
